results.name: Irregular triangle read by rows where T(H(u),H(v)) is the coefficient of s(v) in p(u), where H is Heinz number, p is power sum symmetric functions, and s is Schur functions.
comment: The Heinz number of an integer partition (y_1, ..., y_k) is prime(y_1) * ... * prime(y_k).
example: For example, row 12 gives: p(211) = s(4) + s(31) - s(211) - s(1111).
results.author: _Gus Wiseman_, Nov 20 2018
